                "invention-title": "Process and plant for producing vinyl chloride from 1,2-dichloroethane"
            },
            "abstract": {
                "p": "The present invention relates to a process for producing vinyl chloride by catalytic thermal cleavage of 1,2-dichloroethane, in which the heat required for the thermal cleavage is supplied via a liquid heat-transfer medium or condensing heat-transfer medium (4), wherein, according to the invention, the heat-transfer medium (4) is heated at least partly by means of the thermal energy produced in the oxidation of hydrogen (10), ammonia (11) or a hydrogen-ammonia mixture. The invention additionally provides a plant for producing vinyl chloride by catalytic thermal cleavage of 1,2-dichloroethane, comprising at least one reactor (1) in which the thermal cleavage takes place and also at least one first heating device (6) by means of which the reaction medium (13) is heated in the reactor (1) by the heat-transfer medium (4), the at least one first heating device (6) being designed for an oxidation of hydrogen (10) and/or ammonia (11), for example a combustion of hydrogen (10) and/or ammonia (11), whereby thermal energy that can be used to heat the heat-transfer medium (4) is generated."
